  Ryser's Conjecture

  Domain: mathematics
  ID: opa.mathematics.combinatorics.rysers-conjecture
  Status: Open

  In an n x n Latin square (where each symbol appears exactly once in each row and column), can you always find n entries, one per row and one per column, that are all different? Ryser conjectured yes when n is odd; the Brualdi-Stein extension asks for n - 1 such entries in all cases.

-/

